23/11/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Ministry Chief Secretary General Boyko Borisov said Friday (21 November) that foreign anti-terrorism experts are staying in Sofia for talks on security. 
Local media reported that experts from the United States, Britain, Israel and Turkey arrived in the Bulgarian capital in the wake of deadly terrorist strikes in neighbouring Turkey. 
Bulgaria has started implementing all recommendations, Borisov said.
In other news, Turkish Ambassador to Sofia Haydar Berk told the local radio station Darik that the Bulgarian and Turkish security services have "very serious and close co-operation". 
He added that there had been no information about threats against Bulgaria in the context of attacks in his country. 
(Sega, Dnevnik, BTA - 22/11/03)
